  "prompt": "How long will it take for India to become a cashless economy?",
  "response": "There's no definitive timeline for India becoming a fully cashless economy, but progress has been made since the 2016 demonetization. Experts and government sources suggest different perspectives:\n\n1. Current Status:\n- Cash still dominates around 70-80% of transactions\n- Digital payments are increasing gradually\n- Government promoting digital transactions through various initiatives\n\n2. Potential Timelines:\n- Optimistic estimates suggest 10-15 years\n- Conservative estimates range from 20-25 years\n- Complete cashless transition is challenging due to:\n  - Large unbanked population\n  - Limited digital infrastructure in rural areas\n  - Digital literacy gaps\n  - Cash dependency in informal sectors\n\n3. Ongoing Efforts:\n- Digital India program\n- Promotion of digital payment platforms\n- Incentivizing digital transactions\n- Expanding digital banking infrastructure\n- Increasing digital financial literacy\n\n4. Challenges:\n- Rural connectivity\n- Technological barriers\n- Cultural preferences for cash\n- Income disparities\n- Limited smartphone penetration\n\nWhile complete cashlessness seems unlikely in the near future, India is steadily moving towards a less-cash economy with increasing digital financial inclusion.",
